*********************************************************************** 00150003
*                                                                     * 00200003
* MODULE NAME      - IEFJSSNT                                         * 00250003
*                                                                     * 00300003
* DESCRIPTIVE NAME - SUBSYSTEM NAMES TABLE                            * 00350003
*                                                                     * 00400003
* COPYRIGHT        - NONE                                             * 00450003
*                                                                     * 00500003
* STATUS - VS2 SU 16 - IN THIS MODULE, SU 16 SUPPORTS          @G16APPK 00550003
*                    VPSS SUPPORT (SU 29 - @G29ANSS).          @G16APPK 00600003
*                  - NEW FOR VS2 VECTOR PROCESSING SUBSYSTEM          * 00650003
*                    SUPPORT(SU29)                             @G29ANSS 00700003
*                                                                     * 00750003
* FUNCTION         - THIS MODULE (THE SUBSYSTEM NAMES TABLE) CONTAINS * 00800003
*                    A TABLE CONSISTING OF 80 CHARACTER ENTRIES AND   * 00850003
*                    IS FORMATED AS FOLLOWS:                          * 00900003
*                                                                     * 00950003
*                    ________________________________________________ * 01000003
*                    |      |                  |                    | * 01050003
*                    | NAME | ENTRY POINT NAME |  COMMENTS          | * 01100003
*                    |      |                  |                    | * 01150003
*                    ------------------------------------------------ * 01200003
*                    0       4                 12                  79 * 01250003
*                                                                     * 01300003
*                    WHERE :                                          * 01350003
*                       NAME IS:                                      * 01400003
*                          1) A ONE TO FOUR CHARACTER ALPHAMERIC      * 01450003
*                             SUBSYSTEM NAME. IF THE NAME IS LESS     * 01500003
*                             THAN FOUR CHARACTERS IT MUST BE LEFT    * 01550003
*                             JUSTIFIED AND PADDED WITH BLANKS.       * 01600003
*                          OR                                         * 01650003
*                          2) A DUMMY ENTRY SIGNIFIED BY THE FIRST    * 01700003
*                             BYTE OF THE NAME BEING BLANK.           * 01750003
*                          OR                                         * 01800003
*                          3) AN END OF TABLE INDICATION SIGNIFIED BY * 01850003
*                             A NAME FIELD OF X'FFFFFFFF'.            * 01900003
*                                                                     * 01950003
*                       ENTRY POINT NAME IS:                          * 02000003
*                          1) A ONE TO EIGHT CHARACTER ENTRY NAME     * 02050003
*                             CORRESPONDING TO THE ENTRY POINT OF THE * 02100003
*                             INITIALIZATION ROUTINE FOR THE          * 02150003
*                             ASSOCIATED SUBSYSTEM. IF THE NAME IS    * 02200003
*                             LESS THAN EIGHT BYTES IT MUST BE LEFT   * 02250003
*                             JUSTIFIED AND PADDED WITH BLANKS.       * 02300003
*                                                                     * 02350003
*                             THE ENTRY NAME MUST BE A MEMBER NAME OR * 02400003
*                             AN ALIAS IN THE DIRECTORY OF            * 02450003
*                             SYS1.LINKLIB OR A LIBRARY CONCATENATED  * 02500003
*                             TO LINKLIB VIA A LNKSTXX MEMBER OF      * 02550003
*                             SYS1.PARMLIB.                           * 02600003
*                                                                     * 02650003
*                             THE SPECIFIED ENTRY POINT WILL BE       * 02700003
*                             INVOKED USING THE STANDARD CALLING      * 02750003
*                             SEQUENCE TO PASS THE                    * 02800003
*                             CORRESPONDING SSCVT FOR THE SUBSYSTEM.  * 02850003
*                          OR                                         * 02900003
*                          2) A NULL ENTRY NAME INDICATED BY          * 02950003
*                             SPECIFYING THE FIRST CHARACTER OF THE   * 03000003
*                             ENTRY NAME AS BLANK.                    * 03050003
*                                                                     * 03100003
*                       COMMENTS ARE:                                 * 03150003
*                             BYTES 12 THRU 79 OF THE TABLE ENTRY ARE * 03200003
*                             FOR COMMENTS AND ARE IGNORED.           * 03250003
*                                                                     * 03300003
*                                                                     * 03350003
*                    A DUMMY ENTRY IS USED TO RESERVE SPACE IN        * 03400003
*                    THE TABLE. AN SSCVT IS NOT BUILT AND THE         * 03450003
*                    INITIALIZATION ROUTINE WILL NOT BE INVOKED.      * 03500003
*                                                                     * 03550003
*                    A TABLE ENTRY HAVING A VALID NAME FIELD AND A    * 03600003
*                    NULL ENTRY NAME WILL CAUSE ONLY THE SSCVT TO BE  * 03650003
*                    BUILT. NO INITIALIZATION WILL BE DONE.           * 03700003
*                                                                     * 03750003
* NOTES                                                               * 03800003
*      CHARACTER CODE DEPENDENCIES - THIS MODULE HAS BEEN CODED IN    * 03850003
*                    SUCH A WAY THAT IF THE EXTERNAL CHARACTER SET IS * 03900003
*                    CHANGED FROM EBCDIC, REASSEMBLY WILL YIELD A     * 03950003
*                    VALID MODULE.                                    * 04000003
*                                                                     * 04050003
*      PATCH LABEL - PATCH                                            * 04100003
*                                                                     * 04150003
* MODULE TYPE      - CSECT                                            * 04200003
*      PROCESSOR   - ASSEMBLER                                        * 04250003
*      MODULE SIZE - X'246' BYTES                                     * 04300003
*      ATTRIBUTES  - NOT EXECUTABLE. IN LOAD MODULE IEFJSSNT OF THE   * 04350003
*                    SYS1.LINKLIB DATA SET                            * 04400003
*                                                                     * 04450003
* ENTRY POINTS     - NONE                                             * 04500003
*                                                                     * 04550003
* INPUT            - NONE                                             * 04600003
*                                                                     * 04650003
* OUTPUT           - NONE                                             * 04700003
*                                                                     * 04750003
* EXITS-NORMAL     - NONE                                             * 04800003
*                                                                     * 04850003
* EXITS-ERROR      - NONE                                             * 04900003
*                                                                     * 04950003
* EXTERNAL REFERENCES - NONE                                          * 05000003
*                                                                     * 05050003
* TABLES/WORK AREAS - NO EXTERNAL AREAS. THIS IS THE SUBSYSTEM        * 05100003
*                     NAMES TABLE.                                    * 05150003
*                                                                     * 05200003
* CHANGE ACTIVITY  - G29ANSS FOR ALL STATEMENTS NOT OTHERWISE         * 05250003
*                    FLAGGED.                                  @G29ANSS 05300003
*                                                                     * 05350003
* SYSGEN           - THIS MODULE IS INCLUDED AT SYSGEN FROM DLIB      * 05400003
*                    AOSB3 USING SYSGEN MACRO SGIEF440.               * 05450003
*                                                                     * 05500003
* MESSAGES         - NONE                                             * 05550003
*                                                                     * 05600003
* ABEND CODES      - NONE                                             * 05650003
*                                                                     * 05700003
*********************************************************************** 05750003
         EJECT                                                          05800003
*********************************************************************** 05850003
*        1ST DUMMY ENTRY                                              * 05900003
*********************************************************************** 05950003
         DC    CL4' '              SUBSYSTEM NAME FIELD                 06000003
         DC    CL8' '              ENTRY POINT NAME FIELD               06050003
         DC    CL68' '             COMMENT FIELD                        06100003
         SPACE 2                                                        06150003
*********************************************************************** 06200003
*        2ND DUMMY ENTRY                                              * 06250003
*********************************************************************** 06300003
         DC    CL4' '              SUBSYSTEM NAME FIELD                 06350003
         DC    CL8' '              ENTRY POINT NAME FIELD               06400003
         DC    CL68' '             COMMENT FIELD                        06450003
         SPACE 2                                                        06500003
*********************************************************************** 06550003
*        3RD DUMMY ENTRY                                              * 06600003
*********************************************************************** 06650003
         DC    CL4' '              SUBSYSTEM NAME FIELD                 06700003
         DC    CL8' '              ENTRY POINT NAME FIELD               06750003
         DC    CL68' '             COMMENT FIELD                        06800003
         SPACE 2                                                        06850003
*********************************************************************** 06900003
*        4TH DUMMY ENTRY                                              * 06950003
*********************************************************************** 07000003
         DC    CL4' '              SUBSYSTEM NAME FIELD                 07050003
         DC    CL8' '              ENTRY POINT NAME FIELD               07100003
         DC    CL68' '             COMMENT FIELD                        07150003
         SPACE 2                                                        07200003
*********************************************************************** 07250003
*        5TH DUMMY ENTRY                                              * 07300003
*********************************************************************** 07350003
         DC    CL4' '              SUBSYSTEM NAME FIELD                 07400003
         DC    CL8' '              ENTRY POINT NAME FIELD               07450003
         DC    CL68' '             COMMENT FIELD                        07500003
         SPACE 2                                                        07550003
*********************************************************************** 07600003
*        THIS ENTRY CAN NOT BE USED. IT MARKS THE END OF THE TABLE.   * 07650003
*********************************************************************** 07700003
         DC    XL4'FFFFFFFF'                                            07750003
         DC    CL8' '                                                   07800003
         DC    CL68' '                                                  07850003
         SPACE 2                                                        07900003
PATCH    DC    CL80'*** IEFJSSNT PATCH AREA ***'  LENGTH IS SIZE OF    X07950003
                                                  ONE ENTRY             08000003
         SPACE 2                                                        08050003
         MODID BRANCH=NO                                                08100003
         SPACE 2                                                        08150003
         EJECT                                                          08200003
*********************************************************************** 08250003
*        THIS DSECT MAPS AN ENTRY IN MODULE IEFJSSNT                  * 08300003
*********************************************************************** 08350003
JSSNTENT DSECT                                                          08400003
JSSNTNAM DS    CL4                 SUBSYSTEM NAME FIELD                 08450003
JSSNTINT DS    CL8                 INITIALIZATION ENTRY PT. NAME FIELD  08500003
JSSNTCOM DS    CL68                COMMENT FIELD                        08550003
JSSNTLEN EQU   *-JSSNTNAM          LENGTH OF ENTRY IN IEFJSSNT          08600003
         END   IEFJSSNT                                                 08650003
./  ADD  SSI=23212205,NAME=IEFJWRTE
         TITLE 'PSEUDO ACCESS METHOD WRITE A SEQUENTIAL RECORD       '  00001000
IEFJWRTE CSECT ,                                                   0001 00002000
@MAINENT DS    0H                                                  0001 00003000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00004000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00005000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00006000
         DC    C'IEFJWRTE  72.321'                                 0001 00007000
         DROP  @15                                                      00008000
@PROLOG  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0001 00009000
         BALR  @12,0                                               0001 00010000
@PSTART  DS    0H                                                  0001 00011000
         USING @PSTART,@12                                         0001 00012000
         L     @00,@SIZDATD                                        0001 00013000
         GETMAIN R,LV=(0)                                               00014000
         LR    @11,@01                                             0001 00015000
         USING @DATD,@11                                           0001 00016000
         LM    @00,@01,20(@13)                                     0001 00017000
*   RPLPTR=R1;                      /* SAVE THE POINTER TO THE RPL   */ 00018000
         LR    RPLPTR,R1                                           0008 00019000
*   RFY                                                            0009 00020000
*     R1 UNRSTD;                    /* RELEASE R1                    */ 00021000
*   RFY                                                            0010 00022000
*     IFGRPL BASED(RPLPTR);         /* THE RPL MACRO IS BASED ON THE    00023000
*                                      CONTENTS OF RPLPTR            */ 00024000
*   RFY                                                            0011 00025000
*     IFGACB BASED(RPLDACB);        /* THE ACB IS BASED ON A PTR IN     00026000
*                                      THE RPL                       */ 00027000
*   RFY                                                            0012 00028000
*     ACBPRFIX BASED(ADDR(IFGACB)-4);/* GET THE ACB PREFIX           */ 00029000
*   RFY                                                            0013 00030000
*     IEFJAMWD BASED(ACBPRFIX);     /* THE ACCESS METHOD WORK AREA IS   00031000
*                                      BASED ON THE ACB PREFIX       */ 00032000
*   RFY                                                            0014 00033000
*     IEFJAREA BASED(AMWDLAST);     /* THE COMMON DATA RECORD AREA   */ 00034000
*                                                                  0015 00035000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00036000
*   /*                                                               */ 00037000
*   /* PERFORM A SEQUENTIAL WRITE                                    */ 00038000
*   /*                                                               */ 00039000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00040000
*                                                                  0015 00041000
*   TEXTLGTH=RPLRLEN+8;             /* SAVE RECORD LGTH AND ADD 8  0015 00042000
*                                      BYTES FOR A REC PREFIX        */ 00043000
         LA    TEXTLGTH,8                                          0015 00044000
         A     TEXTLGTH,RPLRLEN(,RPLPTR)                           0015 00045000
*   SPNUM=10;                       /* SUBPOOL USED IS 10            */ 00046000
         MVI   SPNUM,X'0A'                                         0016 00047000
*   SPLEN=TEXTLGTH;                 /* TEXTLGTH EQUALS THE SIZE OF 0017 00048000
*                                      CORE REQUIRED                 */ 00049000
         STCM  TEXTLGTH,7,SPLEN                                    0017 00050000
*   RFY                                                            0018 00051000
*    (R0,                                                          0018 00052000
*     R1)RSTD;                      /* RESTRICT R1, R0               */ 00053000
*   R0=R0INPUT;                     /* THE SUBPOOL NUMBER AND LENGTH    00054000
*                                      ARE SET IN R0                 */ 00055000
         L     R0,R0INPUT                                          0019 00056000
*   GEN(GETMAIN R,LV=(0));          /* ISSUE GETMAIN                 */ 00057000
         GETMAIN R,LV=(0)                                               00058000
*   GETMNADD=R1;                    /* SAVE ADDR RETURNED            */ 00059000
         LR    GETMNADD,R1                                         0021 00060000
*   RFY                                                            0022 00061000
*    (R0,                                                          0022 00062000
*     R1)UNRSTD;                    /* RELEASE R0,R1                 */ 00063000
*   IF AMWDFRST¬=0 THEN             /* IS THIS THE FIRST REC IN THE     00064000
*                                      CHAIN                         */ 00065000
         L     @10,RPLDACB(,RPLPTR)                                0023 00066000
         AL    @10,@CF00233                                        0023 00067000
         L     @10,ACBPRFIX(,@10)                                  0023 00068000
         ICM   @07,15,AMWDFRST(@10)                                0023 00069000
         BZ    @RF00023                                            0023 00070000
*     NEXTPTR=GETMNADD;             /* IF NOT CHAIN TO LAST RECORD   */ 00071000
         L     @10,AMWDLAST(,@10)                                  0024 00072000
         ST    GETMNADD,NEXTPTR(,@10)                              0024 00073000
*   ELSE                            /* IF THIS IS THE FIRST REC IN 0025 00074000
*                                      THE CHAIN THEN SET AMWDFRST   */ 00075000
*     AMWDFRST=GETMNADD;            /* EQUAL TO ADDR OF CORE         */ 00076000
         B     @RC00023                                            0025 00077000
@RF00023 L     @10,RPLDACB(,RPLPTR)                                0025 00078000
         AL    @10,@CF00233                                        0025 00079000
         L     @10,ACBPRFIX(,@10)                                  0025 00080000
         ST    GETMNADD,AMWDFRST(,@10)                             0025 00081000
*   AMWDLAST=GETMNADD;              /* BASE RECORD FORMAT ON THE ADDR   00082000
*                                      OF THE GOTTEN AREA            */ 00083000
@RC00023 L     @10,RPLDACB(,RPLPTR)                                0026 00084000
         AL    @10,@CF00233                                        0026 00085000
         L     @10,ACBPRFIX(,@10)                                  0026 00086000
         ST    GETMNADD,AMWDLAST(,@10)                             0026 00087000
*   TEXTPTR=RPLAREA;                /* TEXTPTR NOW POINTS TO THE AREA   00088000
*                                      THAT THE REC WILL BE WRITTEN     00089000
*                                      FROM                          */ 00090000
         L     TEXTPTR,RPLAREA(,RPLPTR)                            0027 00091000
*   RECPTR=ADDR(IEFJAREA);          /* RECPTR POINTS TO THE REC TO BE   00092000
*                                      RE-WRITTEN                    */ 00093000
         L     @10,RPLDACB(,RPLPTR)                                0028 00094000
         AL    @10,@CF00233                                        0028 00095000
         L     @10,ACBPRFIX(,@10)                                  0028 00096000
         L     @10,AMWDLAST(,@10)                                  0028 00097000
         LR    RECPTR,@10                                          0028 00098000
*   IF RPLRLEN<=256 THEN            /* CHECK LENGTH OF REC IF > 256     00099000
*                                      MORE THAN ONE MOVE IS       0029 00100000
*                                      NECESSARY                     */ 00101000
         CLC   RPLRLEN(4,RPLPTR),@CF00232                          0029 00102000
         BH    @RF00029                                            0029 00103000
*     RECTEXT(1:RPLRLEN)=TEXTAREA(1:RPLRLEN);/* LESS THAN 256 MOVE 0030 00104000
*                                      AND END                       */ 00105000
         L     @07,RPLRLEN(,RPLPTR)                                0030 00106000
         BCTR  @07,0                                               0030 00107000
         EX    @07,@SM00234                                        0030 00108000
*   ELSE                                                           0031 00109000
*     DO;                                                          0031 00110000
         B     @RC00029                                            0031 00111000
@RF00029 DS    0H                                                  0032 00112000
*       CTR=RPLRLEN/256;            /* SET CTR TO THE NUMBER OF MOVES   00113000
*                                      NECESSARY                     */ 00114000
         L     CTR,RPLRLEN(,RPLPTR)                                0032 00115000
         SRL   CTR,8                                               0032 00116000
*       DO WHILE CTR>0;             /* EXECUTE UNTIL ALL 256 BYTE  0033 00117000
*                                      BLOCKS HAVE BEEN MOVED        */ 00118000
         B     @DE00033                                            0033 00119000
@DL00033 DS    0H                                                  0034 00120000
*         RECPTR->RECTEXT(1:256)=TEXTAREA(1:256);/* MOVE 256 BYTES AT   00121000
*                                      A TIME                        */ 00122000
         MVC   RECTEXT(256,RECPTR),TEXTAREA(TEXTPTR)               0034 00123000
*         TEXTPTR=TEXTPTR+256;      /* UPDATE POINTER                */ 00124000
         LA    @10,256                                             0035 00125000
         AR    TEXTPTR,@10                                         0035 00126000
*         RECPTR=RECPTR+256;        /* UPDATE POINTER                */ 00127000
         AR    RECPTR,@10                                          0036 00128000
*         CTR=CTR-1;                /* DECREMENT COUNTER             */ 00129000
         BCTR  CTR,0                                               0037 00130000
*       END;                                                       0038 00131000
@DE00033 LTR   CTR,CTR                                             0038 00132000
         BP    @DL00033                                            0038 00133000
*       CTR=RPLRLEN//256;           /* SET REMAINING LENGTH IN CTR   */ 00134000
         L     CTR,RPLRLEN(,RPLPTR)                                0039 00135000
         N     CTR,@CF00236                                        0039 00136000
*       RECPTR->RECTEXT(1:CTR)=TEXTAREA(1:CTR);/* MOVE REMAINING   0040 00137000
*                                      LENGTH                        */ 00138000
         LR    @10,CTR                                             0040 00139000
         BCTR  @10,0                                               0040 00140000
         EX    @10,@SM00237                                        0040 00141000
*     END;                                                         0041 00142000
*   LGTH=TEXTLGTH;                  /* SET THE LENGTH                */ 00143000
@RC00029 L     @10,RPLDACB(,RPLPTR)                                0042 00144000
         AL    @10,@CF00233                                        0042 00145000
         L     @10,ACBPRFIX(,@10)                                  0042 00146000
         L     @10,AMWDLAST(,@10)                                  0042 00147000
         ST    TEXTLGTH,LGTH(,@10)                                 0042 00148000
*   NEXTPTR=0;                      /* THE NEXTPTR IS ALWAYS SET TO     00149000
*                                      ZERO BECAUSE THERE IS NO WAY     00150000
*                                      OF KNOWING IF THIS IS THE LAST   00151000
*                                      REC                           */ 00152000
         SR    @03,@03                                             0043 00153000
         ST    @03,NEXTPTR(,@10)                                   0043 00154000
*   RPLDDDD=ADDR(RECTEXT);          /* RETURN THE ADDR IN THE RPL    */ 00155000
         LA    @10,RECTEXT(,@10)                                   0044 00156000
         ST    @10,RPLDDDD(,RPLPTR)                                0044 00157000
*   END IEFJWRTE                    /* RETURN TO CALLER              */ 00158000
*                                                                  0045 00159000
*/* THE FOLLOWING INCLUDE STATEMENTS WERE FOUND IN THIS PROGRAM.     */ 00160000
*/*%INCLUDE SYSLIB  (IFGACB  )                                       */ 00161000
*/*%INCLUDE SYSLIB  (IFGRPL  )                                       */ 00162000
*/*%INCLUDE SYSLIB  (IEFJAMWD)                                       */ 00163000
*/*%INCLUDE SYSLIB  (IEFJAREA)                                       */ 00164000
*                                                                  0045 00165000
*       ;                                                          0045 00166000
@EL00001 DS    0H                                                  0045 00167000
@EF00001 L     @00,@SIZDATD                                        0045 00168000
         LR    @01,@11                                             0045 00169000
         FREEMAIN R,LV=(0),A=(1)                                        00170000
@ER00001 LM    @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0045 00171000
         BR    @14                                                 0045 00172000
@DATA    DS    0H                                                       00173000
@SM00234 MVC   RECTEXT(0,@10),TEXTAREA(TEXTPTR)                         00174000
@SM00237 MVC   RECTEXT(0,RECPTR),TEXTAREA(TEXTPTR)                      00175000
@DATD    DSECT                                                          00176000
         DS    0F                                                       00177000
IEFJWRTE CSECT                                                          00178000
         DS    0F                                                       00179000
@CF00233 DC    F'-4'                                                    00180000
@CF00236 DC    F'255'                                                   00181000
@CF00232 DC    F'256'                                                   00182000
@DATD    DSECT                                                          00183000
         DS    0D                                                       00184000
R0INPUT  DS    CL4                                                      00185000
         ORG   R0INPUT                                                  00186000
SPNUM    DS    FL1                                                      00187000
SPLEN    DS    FL3                                                      00188000
         ORG   R0INPUT+4                                                00189000
@ENDDATD EQU   *                                                        00190000
IEFJWRTE CSECT                                                          00191000
         DS    0F                                                       00192000
@SIZDATD DC    AL1(0)                                                   00193000
         DC    AL3(@ENDDATD-@DATD)                                      00194000
         DS    0D                                                       00195000

./  ADD  SSI=33441075,NAME=IEFJWTOM
         TITLE 'IEFJWTOM - IEFJWTOM MESSAGE WTO ROUTINE                *00001000

IEFJWTOM CSECT ,                                                   0001 00003000
@MAINENT BALR  @15,0                                               0001 00004000
         USING *,@15                                               0001 00005000
         B     @PROLOG                                             0001 00006000
         DC    AL1(16)                                             0001 00007000
         DC    C'IEFJWTOM  73.344'                                 0001 00008000
         DROP  @15                                                      00009000
@PROLOG  STM   @14,@12,12(@13)                                     0001 00010000
         BALR  @12,0                                               0001 00011000
@PSTART  DS    0H                                                  0001 00012000
         USING @PSTART,@12                                         0001 00013000
*                                                                  0042 00014000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00015000
*   /*                                                               */ 00016000
*   /* IF REGISTER 1 IS ZERO,THEN ABEND WITH 0B1 ABEND.              */ 00017000
*   /*                                                               */ 00018000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00019000
*                                                                  0042 00020000
*   IF REG1=0 THEN                                                 0042 00021000
         LTR   REG1,REG1                                           0042 00022000
         BNZ   @RF00042                                            0042 00023000
*     GEN(ABEND 177,,,SYSTEM);                                     0043 00024000
*                                                                  0043 00025000
         ABEND 177,,,SYSTEM                                             00026000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00027000
*   /*                                                               */ 00028000
*   /* INITIALIZE RPL POINTER FROM REGISTER 1                        */ 00029000
*   /*                                                               */ 00030000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00031000
*                                                                  0044 00032000
*   RPLPTR=REG1;                                                   0044 00033000
@RF00042 LR    RPLPTR,REG1                                         0044 00034000
*   RESPECIFY                                                      0045 00035000
*     IFGRPL BASED(RPLPTR);                                        0045 00036000
*                                                                  0045 00037000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00038000
*   /*                                                               */ 00039000
*   /* VALIDITY CHECK RPL FIELDS - RPLAREA,RPLRLEN. IF EITHER IS     */ 00040000
*   /* ZERO,THEN SET LOGICAL ERROR RETURN IN REGISTER 15 AND         */ 00041000
*   /* ILLOGICAL REQUEST ERROR IN RPLRTNCD.                          */ 00042000
*   /*                                                               */ 00043000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00044000
*                                                                  0046 00045000
*   IF RPLAREA=0|RPLRLEN=0 THEN                                    0046 00046000
         SLR   @15,@15                                             0046 00047000
         C     @15,RPLAREA(,RPLPTR)                                0046 00048000
         BE    @RT00046                                            0046 00049000
         C     @15,RPLRLEN(,RPLPTR)                                0046 00050000
         BNE   @RF00046                                            0046 00051000
@RT00046 DS    0H                                                  0047 00052000
*     DO;                                                          0047 00053000
*       RTNCDE=8;                   /* LOGICAL ERROR RETURN IN R15   */ 00054000
         LA    RTNCDE,8                                            0048 00055000
*       RPLRTNCD=8;                 /* ILLOGICAL REQUEST RETURN IN 0049 00056000
*                                      RPL                           */ 00057000
         MVI   RPLRTNCD(RPLPTR),X'08'                              0049 00058000
*       RPLERRCD=RPLINLRQ;          /* INCORRECT REQUEST             */ 00059000
         MVI   RPLERRCD(RPLPTR),X'74'                              0050 00060000
*     END;                                                         0051 00061000
*   ELSE                                                           0052 00062000
*     DO;                                                          0052 00063000
*                                                                  0052 00064000
         B     @RC00046                                            0052 00065000
@RF00046 DS    0H                                                  0053 00066000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00067000
*       /*                                                           */ 00068000
*       /* INITIALIZE MESSAGE POINTER FROM RPL                       */ 00069000
*       /*                                                           */ 00070000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00071000
*                                                                  0053 00072000
*       MSGPTR=RPLAREA;                                            0053 00073000
*                                                                  0053 00074000
         L     MSGPTR,RPLAREA(,RPLPTR)                             0053 00075000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00076000
*       /*                                                           */ 00077000
*       /* INITIALIZE MESSAGE LENGTH FROM RPL                        */ 00078000
*       /*                                                           */ 00079000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00080000
*                                                                  0054 00081000
*       MSGLEN=RPLRLEN;                                            0054 00082000
*                                                                  0054 00083000
         L     MSGLEN,RPLRLEN(,RPLPTR)                             0054 00084000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00085000
*       /*                                                           */ 00086000
*       /* SET RETURN CODE IN RPL AND R15 TO ZERO                    */ 00087000
*       /*                                                           */ 00088000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00089000
*                                                                  0055 00090000
*       RPLRTNCD=0;                                                0055 00091000
         MVI   RPLRTNCD(RPLPTR),X'00'                              0055 00092000
*       RTNCDE=0;                                                  0056 00093000
*                                                                  0056 00094000
         SLR   RTNCDE,RTNCDE                                       0056 00095000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00096000
*       /*                                                           */ 00097000
*       /* GET WTO LIST FORM BUFFER                                  */ 00098000
*       /*                                                           */ 00099000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00100000
*                                                                  0057 00101000
*/*       ADCON FOR WTOLIST LENGTH HAS HIGH ORDER BYTE OF ZERO.230 0057 00102000
*         SERVES AS SUBPOOL NUMBER FOR GETMAIN AND FREEMAIN.         */ 00103000
*                                                                  0057 00104000
*       REG0=WTOLEN;                                               0057 00105000
         L     REG0,WTOLEN                                         0057 00106000
*       REG0=REG0|SPNUMBER;         /* 230 INTO HIGH ORDER BYTE    0058 00107000
*                                                            @YM02481*/ 00108000
         O     REG0,SPNUMBER                                       0058 00109000
*       GEN(GETMAIN R,LV=(0));                                     0059 00110000
         GETMAIN R,LV=(0)                                               00111000
*       WPLPTR=REG1;                /* SET UP ADDRESSABILITY FOR LIST*/ 00112000
*                                                                  0060 00113000
         LR    WPLPTR,REG1                                         0060 00114000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00115000
*       /*                                                           */ 00116000
*       /* INITIALIZE GOTTEN CORE WITH LIST EXPANDED IN CSECT        */ 00117000
*       /*                                                           */ 00118000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00119000
*                                                                  0061 00120000
*       WTOCORE(1:WTOLEN)=WTOCSECT(1:WTOLEN);                      0061 00121000
*                                                                  0061 00122000
         L     @15,WTOLEN                                          0061 00123000
         BCTR  @15,0                                               0061 00124000
         EX    @15,@SM00367                                        0061 00125000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00126000
*       /*                                                           */ 00127000
*       /* MOVE MESSAGE ID INTO MESSAGE BUFFER IN WTO LIST           */ 00128000
*       /*                                                           */ 00129000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00130000
*                                                                  0062 00131000
*       WPLTXT(1:8)=MSGID;                                         0062 00132000
*                                                                  0062 00133000
         MVC   WPLTXT(8,WPLPTR),MSGID                              0062 00134000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00135000
*       /*                                                           */ 00136000
*       /* ADD LENGTH OF TWO FIELDS PRECEEDING MESSAGE TEXT IN WTO   */ 00137000
*       /* MACRO EXPANSION TO GET LENGTH OF MESSAGE, THEN SUBTRACT   */ 00138000
*       /* LENGTH OF MESSAGE ID.                                     */ 00139000
*       /*                                                           */ 00140000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00141000
*                                                                  0063 00142000
*       TEXTLEN=WPLLGH-(LENGTH(WPLLGH)+LENGTH(WPLMCSF)+LENGTH(MSGID));  00143000
*                                                                  0063 00144000
         LH    TEXTLEN,WPLLGH(,WPLPTR)                             0063 00145000
         SH    TEXTLEN,@CH00167                                    0063 00146000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00147000
*       /*                                                           */ 00148000
*       /* SCAN MESSAGE BACKWARDS FOR BLANKS.TRUNCATE TRAILING       */ 00149000
*       /* BLANKS.                                                   */ 00150000
*       /*                                                           */ 00151000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00152000
*                                                                  0064 00153000
*       MSGLEN=MSGLEN-1;            /* SUBTRACT 1 FOR BACK SCAN      */ 00154000
         BCTR  MSGLEN,0                                            0064 00155000
*       DO MSGLEN TO 0 BY-1 WHILE SCANBLNK='40'X;                  0065 00156000
         B     @DE00065                                            0065 00157000
@DL00065 LR    @15,MSGPTR                                          0065 00158000
         ALR   @15,MSGLEN                                          0065 00159000
         CLI   SCANBLNK(@15),X'40'                                 0065 00160000
         BNE   @DC00065                                            0065 00161000
*       END;                                                       0066 00162000
*                                                                  0066 00163000
         BCTR  MSGLEN,0                                            0066 00164000
@DE00065 LTR   MSGLEN,MSGLEN                                       0066 00165000
         BNM   @DL00065                                            0066 00166000
@DC00065 DS    0H                                                  0067 00167000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00168000
*       /*                                                           */ 00169000
*       /* PRECEDING LOOP REDUCES MSGLEN TO LENGTH OF MSG MINUS 1    */ 00170000
*       /*                                                           */ 00171000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00172000
*                                                                  0067 00173000
*       MSGLEN=MSGLEN+1;                                           0067 00174000
*                                                                  0067 00175000
         AH    MSGLEN,@CH00046                                     0067 00176000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00177000
*       /*                                                           */ 00178000
*       /* A MESSAGE LENGTH OF ZERO,MEANING A BLANK MESSAGE,WILL     */ 00179000
*       /* RETURN A LOGICAL ERROR IN REG 15, AND AN ILLOGICAL REQUEST*/ 00180000
*       /* CODE IN THE RPL.                                          */ 00181000
*       /*                                                           */ 00182000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00183000
*                                                                  0068 00184000
*       IF MSGLEN=0 THEN                                           0068 00185000
         LTR   MSGLEN,MSGLEN                                       0068 00186000
         BNZ   @RF00068                                            0068 00187000
*         DO;                                                      0069 00188000
*           RTNCDE=8;                                              0070 00189000
         LA    RTNCDE,8                                            0070 00190000
*           RPLRTNCD=8;                                            0071 00191000
         MVI   RPLRTNCD(RPLPTR),X'08'                              0071 00192000
*           RPLERRCD=RPLINLEN;      /* INVALID LENGTH PASSED         */ 00193000
         MVI   RPLERRCD(RPLPTR),X'6C'                              0072 00194000
*         END;                                                     0073 00195000
*       ELSE                                                       0074 00196000
*         DO;                                                      0074 00197000
         B     @RC00068                                            0074 00198000
@RF00068 DS    0H                                                  0075 00199000
*                                                                  0075 00200000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00201000
*           /*                                                       */ 00202000
*           /* SCAN MESSAGE FOR CHARACTERS OTHER THAN ALPHA-NUMERIC  */ 00203000
*           /* IN ORDER TO FIND A BREAKING POINT.IF MESSAGE IS LESS  */ 00204000
*           /* THAN MAXIMUM ALLOWED,THEN JUST ISSUE ONE MESSAGE.     */ 00205000
*           /*                                                       */ 00206000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00207000
*                                                                  0075 00208000
*           DO WHILE MSGLEN>TEXTLEN;                               0075 00209000
*                                                                  0075 00210000
         B     @DE00075                                            0075 00211000
@DL00075 DS    0H                                                  0076 00212000
*             /*******************************************************/ 00213000
*             /*                                                     */ 00214000
*             /* SCAN BACKWARDS FROM THE MAXIMUM LENGTH OF MESSAGE TO*/ 00215000
*             /* THE BEGINNING TO FIND THE SPECIAL CHARACTER TO BREAK*/ 00216000
*             /* FOR THE SECOND MESSAGE.IF NO SPECIAL CHARACTERS     */ 00217000
*             /* EXIST,PLACE THE MAXIMUM NUMBER OF CHARACTERS IN THE */ 00218000
*             /* BUFFER AND ISSUE WTO.                               */ 00219000
*             /*                                                     */ 00220000
*             /*******************************************************/ 00221000
*                                                                  0076 00222000
*             LGNTH=TEXTLEN-1;      /* LENGTH OF MAXIMUM MESSAGE FOR    00223000
*                                      WTO MINUS 1 FOR BACKWARD SCAN */ 00224000
         LR    LGNTH,TEXTLEN                                       0076 00225000
         BCTR  LGNTH,0                                             0076 00226000
*             DO LGNTH TO 0 BY-1 WHILE SCANCHAR¬=' '&SCANCHAR¬=',';     00227000
         B     @DE00077                                            0077 00228000
@DL00077 LR    @15,MSGPTR                                          0077 00229000
         ALR   @15,LGNTH                                           0077 00230000
         CLI   SCANCHAR(@15),C' '                                  0077 00231000
         BE    @DC00077                                            0077 00232000
         CLI   SCANCHAR(@15),C','                                  0077 00233000
         BE    @DC00077                                            0077 00234000
*             END;                                                 0078 00235000
         BCTR  LGNTH,0                                             0078 00236000
@DE00077 LTR   LGNTH,LGNTH                                         0078 00237000
         BNM   @DL00077                                            0078 00238000
@DC00077 DS    0H                                                  0079 00239000
*             IF LGNTH<0 THEN                                      0079 00240000
         LTR   LGNTH,LGNTH                                         0079 00241000
         BNM   @RF00079                                            0079 00242000
*               LGNTH=TEXTLEN;      /* LENGHT IS MAXIMUM WITH NO   0080 00243000
*                                      SP.CHAR                       */ 00244000
         LR    LGNTH,TEXTLEN                                       0080 00245000
*             ELSE                                                 0081 00246000
*               LGNTH=LGNTH+1;      /* ADD ONE BECAUSE OF BACKWARD 0081 00247000
*                                      SCAN                          */ 00248000
*                                                                  0081 00249000
         B     @RC00079                                            0081 00250000
@RF00079 AH    LGNTH,@CH00046                                      0081 00251000
*             /*******************************************************/ 00252000
*             /*                                                     */ 00253000
*             /* PUT LENGTH OF MESSAGE INTO WTO LIST.ADD LENGTH OF   */ 00254000
*             /* FOUR BYTE WTO LIST HEADER AND EIGHT BYTE MESSAGE ID.*/ 00255000
*             /*                                                     */ 00256000
*             /*******************************************************/ 00257000
*                                                                  0082 00258000
*             WPLLGH=LGNTH+12;      /* PUT ACTUAL LENGTH INTO WTO  0082 00259000
*                                      LIST                          */ 00260000
@RC00079 LA    @15,12                                              0082 00261000
         ALR   @15,LGNTH                                           0082 00262000
         STH   @15,WPLLGH(,WPLPTR)                                 0082 00263000
*             WPLTXT(9:LGNTH+8)=MSGBUF(1:LGNTH);/* MOVE MESSAGE IN   */ 00264000
*                                                                  0083 00265000
         LR    @15,LGNTH                                           0083 00266000
         BCTR  @15,0                                               0083 00267000
         EX    @15,@SM00369                                        0083 00268000
*             /*******************************************************/ 00269000
*             /*                                                     */ 00270000
*             /* ISSUE WTO                                           */ 00271000
*             /*                                                     */ 00272000
*             /*******************************************************/ 00273000
*                                                                  0084 00274000
*             GEN(WTO MF=(E,(2)));                                 0084 00275000
*                                                                  0084 00276000
         WTO MF=(E,(2))                                                 00277000
*             /*******************************************************/ 00278000
*             /*                                                     */ 00279000
*             /* RESET MSGPTR AND MSGLEN TO REFLECT REMAINING PORTION*/ 00280000
*             /* OF THE MESSAGE.                                     */ 00281000
*             /*                                                     */ 00282000
*             /*******************************************************/ 00283000
*                                                                  0085 00284000
*             MSGPTR=MSGPTR+LGNTH;  /* ADJUST MSGPTR FOR REST OF MSG */ 00285000
         ALR   MSGPTR,LGNTH                                        0085 00286000
*             MSGLEN=MSGLEN-LGNTH;  /* ADJUST MSGLEN FOR REST OF MSG */ 00287000
         SLR   MSGLEN,LGNTH                                        0086 00288000
*           END;                                                   0087 00289000
@DE00075 CR    MSGLEN,TEXTLEN                                      0087 00290000
         BH    @DL00075                                            0087 00291000
*                                                                  0088 00292000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00293000
*           /*                                                       */ 00294000
*           /* PUT OUT LAST MESSAGE,OR FIRST MESSAGE IF IT IS LESS   */ 00295000
*           /* THAN THE LENGTH OF THE BUFFER. MOVE MESSAGE           */ 00296000
*           /*                                                       */ 00297000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00298000
*                                                                  0088 00299000
*           WPLTXT(9:MSGLEN+8)=MSGBUF(1:MSGLEN);                   0088 00300000
*                                                                  0088 00301000
         LR    @06,MSGLEN                                          0088 00302000
         BCTR  @06,0                                               0088 00303000
         EX    @06,@SM00369                                        0088 00304000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00305000
*           /*                                                       */ 00306000
*           /* LENGTH OF MESSAGE IS ACTUAL LENGTH IN MSGLEN PLUS THE */ 00307000
*           /* LENGTH OF THE FOUR BYTE WTO LIST HEADER AND THE EIGHT */ 00308000
*           /* BYTE MESSAGE ID.                                      */ 00309000
*           /*                                                       */ 00310000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00311000
*                                                                  0089 00312000
*           WPLLGH=MSGLEN+12;                                      0089 00313000
*                                                                  0089 00314000
         LA    @06,12                                              0089 00315000
         ALR   @06,MSGLEN                                          0089 00316000
         STH   @06,WPLLGH(,WPLPTR)                                 0089 00317000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00318000
*           /*                                                       */ 00319000
*           /* ISSUE WTO                                             */ 00320000
*           /*                                                       */ 00321000
*           /*********************************************************/ 00322000
*                                                                  0090 00323000
*           GEN(WTO MF=(E,(2)));                                   0090 00324000
         WTO MF=(E,(2))                                                 00325000
*         END;                                                     0091 00326000
*                                                                  0091 00327000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00328000
*       /*                                                           */ 00329000
*       /* FREE WTO BUFFER                                           */ 00330000
*       /*                                                           */ 00331000
*       /*************************************************************/ 00332000
*                                                                  0092 00333000
*       REG0=WTOLEN;                                               0092 00334000
@RC00068 L     REG0,WTOLEN                                         0092 00335000
*       REG0=REG0|SPNUMBER;         /* 230 INTO HIGH ORDER BYTE    0093 00336000
*                                                            @YM02481*/ 00337000
         O     REG0,SPNUMBER                                       0093 00338000
*       REG1=WPLPTR;                                               0094 00339000
         LR    REG1,WPLPTR                                         0094 00340000
*       GEN(FREEMAIN R,LV=(0),A=(1));                              0095 00341000
         FREEMAIN R,LV=(0),A=(1)                                        00342000
*     END;                                                         0096 00343000
*                                                                  0096 00344000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00345000
*   /*                                                               */ 00346000
*   /* RETURN TO CALLER WITH RETURN CODE IN R15                      */ 00347000
*   /*                                                               */ 00348000
*   /*****************************************************************/ 00349000
*                                                                  0097 00350000
*   RETURN CODE(RTNCDE);                                           0097 00351000
@RC00046 LR    @15,RTNCDE                                          0097 00352000
         L     @14,12(,@13)                                        0097 00353000
         LM    @00,@12,20(@13)                                     0097 00354000
         BR    @14                                                 0097 00355000
*   END IEFJWTOM                    /* END OF MODULE               0098 00356000
*                                                                    */ 00357000
*                                                                  0098 00358000

@DATA    DS    0H                                                       00366000

./  ADD  SSI=20820062,NAME=IEFRSTRT
IEFRSTRT CSECT                                                          03000017
*                                                                       06000017
*******************************************************************     09000017
*                                                                 *     12000017
* NAME         IEFRSTRT                                           *     15000017
*                                                                 *     18000017
* FUNCTION     TO INVOKE SVC 52, CAUSING RESTART TO OCCUR         *     21000017
*                                                                 *     24000017
* INPUT        NONE                                               *     27000017
*                                                                 *     30000017
* OUTPUT       NONE                                               *     33000017
*                                                                 *     36000017
* BASIC FLOW   ISSUE SVC 52                                       *     39000017
*                                                                 *     42000017
* ENTRY        FROM INITIATOR AS A PROBLEM PROGRAM                *     45000017
*                                                                 *     48000017
* EXIT         TO SVC 52.  SVC 52 WILL OVERLAY THE MAIN STORAGE   *     51000017
*              OCCUPIED BY IEFRSTRT WITH THE MAIN STORAGE IMAGE   *     54000017
*              OF THE RESTARTING STEP WHICH WAS SAVED IN THE      *     57000017
*              CHECKPOINT DATA SET.  THUS, UNLESS THERE IS AN I/O *     60000017
*              ERROR DURING RETRIEVAL OF THE FIRST MAIN STORAGE   *     63000017
*              IMAGE RECORD, THERE WILL BE NO RETURN TO IEFRSTRT  *     66000017
*                                                                 *     69000017
* ATTRIBUTGS   RE-ENTRANT                                         *     72000017
*                                                                 *     75000017
*******************************************************************     78000017
*                                                                       81000017
         SVC 52                        INVOKE RESTART SVC               84000017
         BR 14                         RETURN-ERROR                     87000017
         END                                                            90000017
./  ADD  SSI=72700120,NAME=IEFSD101
         TITLE 'IEFSD101, PPT SCAN'                                     00050002
IEFSD101 CSECT                                                   Y01054 00100000
*        SEE CHANGE ACTIVITY IN PROLOG FOR FLAGGING INFORMATION.        00110002
* C-STATEMENTS NEAR LABEL LPPT8                                @ZA03944 00115041
* A STATEMENTS NEAR LABEL SKIPKEY                              @ZA11857 00120041
* A STATEMENTS NEAR LABEL LPPT3                                @ZA11857 00125041
* DELETED STATEMENTS THAT WERE ADDED FOR @ZA11857              @ZA16879 00133041
* CHANGED STATEMENT NEAR LPPT3 AND ADDED STATEMENTS NEAR LPPT9 @ZA16879 00138041
* C STATEMENTS AFTER LABEL CONTINUE                            @ZA20168 00144041
         BALR  R12,0                                                    00150000
*                                                                     * 00200000
*********************************************************************** 00450000
*                                                                     * 00500000
*     MODULE NAME = IEFSD101                                            00550002
*                                                                       00600002
*     DESCRIPTIVE NAME = PPT SCAN                                       00650002
*                                                                       00660002
*     COPYRIGHT = NONE                                                  00670002
*                                                                       00700002
*     STATUS = SU7 PTF                                         @ZA20168 00720041
*                                                                       00800002
*     FUNCTION = TO SCAN THE PROGRAM PROPERTIES TABLE (PPT),            00850002
*     ASSIGN SPECIAL PROPERTIES WHERE INDICATED, AND BUILD THE          00860002
*     GETPART WORK TABLE (GWT).                                         00900002
*                                                                       00950002
*      OPERATION:                                                       01000002
*                                                                       01050002
*      1) CALL IEFSMFIE FOR SMF PROCESSING.                             01100002
*                                                                       01160002
*      1A) SET UP FIELDS CHSTEP AND CHPROCSN FOR USE BY         YM06960 01170002
*      THE PROCESSOR OF DISPLAY A.                              YM06960 01180002
*                                                                       01200002
*      2) IF THE STEP IS TO RUN IN V=R, MOVE THE PROTECT KEY IN         01250002
*      THE JCT TO THE TCB. IF THE STEP IS TO RUN IN V=V, MOVE A         01300002
*      PROTECT KEY OF 8 TO THE TCB. (THE KEY WILL BE PROPOGATED         01350002
*      WHEN THE DAUGHTER IS ATTACHED.)                                  01400002
*                                                                       01450002
*      3) BEFORE ASSIGNING ANY SPECIAL PROPERTIES TURN OFF ALL          01500002
*      PROPERTIES WHICH MAY HAVE BEEN SET FOR A PREVIOUS STEP.          01510002
*      THEN SCAN THE PPT FOR THE PROGRAM NAME. IF                       01520002
*      NOT FOUND, SKIP TO STEP 4. IF FOUND, SET AN INDICATOR            01530002
*      IN THE LCT THAT THE NAME WAS IN THE PPT.                         01540002
*                                                                       01542002
*         A) IF THE 'NON-CANCELABLE' PROPERTY IS INDICATED, SET         01544002
*         AN INDICATOR IN THE LCT AND SET THE CSCB NON-                 01546002
*         CANCELABLE.                                                   01546402
*                                                                       01546802
*         B) IF A SPECIAL PROTECT KEY IS INDICATED, MOVE THE     Y02656 01547202
*         PROTECT KEY FROM THE PPT TO THE CURRENT TCB. (THIS     Y02656 01547602
*         WILL OVERLAY THE KEY PREVIOUSLY SET.)                  Y02656 01547702
*                                                                       01548502
*         C) IF THE PROGRAM NAME IS AUTHORIZED TO BE NON-        Y02669 01548602
*         SWAPPABLE, SET THE CORRESPONDING INDICATOR IN THE      Y02669 01548702
*         LCT.                                                 @ZA16879 01549241
*                                                                       01550402
*         D) IF THE PROGRAM NAME IS 'PRIVILEGED' (WITH RESPECT   Y02655 01552402
*         TO THE SYSTEM RESOURCES MANAGER) SET AN INDICATOR IN   Y02655 01552502
*         THE LCT.                                               Y02655 01552902
*                                                                       01554502
*         E) IF THE 'SYSTEM TASK' PROPERTY IS INDICATED AND THE  Y02652 01556502
*         JOB IS 'STARTED' AND '1-STEP', SET THE SYSTEM TASK     Y02652 01556602
*         INDICATOR IN THE LCT. IF THE 'SYSTEM TASK' PROPERTY    Y02652 01556702
*         IS INDICATED BUT THE OTHER TWO CONDITIONS ARE NOT MET, Y02652 01557202
*         SET THE INDICATOR IN THE LCT WHICH INDICATES THAT      Y02652 01557602
*         IEFSD162 SHOULD ISSUE MESSAGE IEF188I PROBLEM PROGRAM  Y02652 01558002
*         ATTRIBUTES ASSIGNED.                                   Y02652 01558102
*                                                                       01558402
*         F) IF THE 'NO DATA SET INTEGRITY' (NDSI) PROPERTY IS   Y02652 01558802
*         INDICATED AND THE JOB IS 1-STEP, SET THE INDICATOR IN  Y02652 01559202
*         THE LCT WHICH INDICATES THAT 'NO DATA SET INTEGRITY'   Y02652 01559302
*         HAS BEEN REQUESTED. IF THERE IS NO UNAUTHORIZED JOBLIB Y02652 01559402
*         OR STEPLIB, THE PROPERTY WILL BE ASSIGNED BY IEFSD162. Y02652 01560602
*         IF THE NDSI PROPERTY IS INDICATED AND THE JOB IS MULTI-Y02652 01565402
*         STEP, SET THE INDICATOR IN THE LCT WHICH INDICATES     Y02652 01566602
*         THAT IEFSD162 SHOULD ISSUE MESSAGE IEF188I PROBLEM     Y02652 01567802
*         PROGRAM ATTRIBUTES ASSIGNED. THEN PROCEED TO STEP 4.   Y02652 01569002
*                                                                       01569102
*         G. IF THIS IS THE FIRST STEP OF A JOB, CONTINUE WITH   Y02651 01569402
*         STEP H, BECAUSE TASK AFFINITY IS SET ELSEWHERE FOR THE Y02651 01569502
*         FIRST STEP. IF THE MASK FOR CPU-TASK AFFINITY IS ALL   Y02651 01569802
*         BINARY 1'S, CONTINUE WITH STEP H (BECAUSE NO SPECIAL   Y02651 01569902
*         CPU IS REQUIRED FOR THAT PROGRAM). IF NOT ALL BINARY   Y02651 01570002
*         1'S, INVOKE IEFICPUA TO SET THE AFFINITY IN THE ASCB.  Y02651 01570102
*         IF THE RETURN CODE IS 0, CONTINUE WITH STEP H. IF THE  Y02651 01571502
*         RETURN CODE IS NON-ZERO, SET THE JOB FAILED INDICATOR  Y02651 01571902
*         IN THE JCT AND ISSUE MESSAGE IEF173I, TO INDICATE      Y02651 01572302
*         THAT THE JOB HAS BEEN FAILED.                          Y02651 01572702
*         (IEFIMASK IS INVOKED TO CONVERT THE 16-BIT MASK OF     Y02651 01573102
*         CPU'S REQUIRED FOR AFFINITY TO THE LIST OF CPU ID'S    Y02651 01574202
*         WHICH IS REQUIRED FOR THE MESSAGE.)                    Y02651 01576202
*                                                                       01578202
*         H. IF THE PROPERTY 'BYPASS PASSWORD PROTECTION' IS     Y02656 01579002
*         INDICATED, SET THE CORRESPONDING INDICATOR IN THE      Y02656 01580102
*         JSCB.                                                  Y02656 01581202
*                                                              @ZA16879 01581341
*         I. IF THE PROPERTY 'FIRST LEVEL PREFERRED USAGE'     @ZA16879 01581441
*         IS INDICATED, SET THE CORRESPONDING INDICATOR IN     @ZA16879 01581541
*         THE LCT.                                             @ZA16879 01581641
*                                                              @ZA16879 01581741
*         J. IF THE PROPERTY 'SECOND LEVEL PREFERRED USAGE'    @ZA16879 01581841
*         IS INDICATED, SET BOTH THE FIRST AND SECOND LEVEL    @ZA16879 01581941
*         PREFERRED USAGE INDICATORS IN THE LCT.               @ZA16879 01582041
*                                                              @ZA16879 01582141
*         K. IF THE PROPERTY 'NOT SECOND LEVEL PREFERRED       @ZA16879 01582241
*         USAGE' IS INDICATED, SET THE CORRESPONDING INDICATOR @ZA16879 01582341
*         IN THE LCT.                                          @ZA16879 01582441
*                                                                       01583641
*      3A. IF THIS IS A CHECKPOINT RESTART JOB STEP, THE SCT   @ZA20168 01584241
*      PROGRAM NAME FIELD WILL BE CHANGED TO IEFRSTRT WHICH    @ZA20168 01584341
*      INVOKES THE RESTART SVC. THE RESTART SVC COMPLETES      @ZA20168 01584441
*      RESTART PROCESSING. THIS IS DONE AFTER PPT PROCESSING   @ZA20168 01584541
*      IS COMPLETE FOR REAL PROGRAM NAME.                      @ZA20168 01584641
*                                                                       01584741
*      4. THE GETPART WORK TABLE (GWT) IS THEN BUILT, BUT ONLY   Y02669 01584841
*      IF THE CURRENT STEP IS TO BE EXECUTED AND ONE OF THE      Y02669 01584941
*      FOLLOWING IS TRUE:                                        Y02669 01585602
